Cross River State government has called on widows of fallen heroes and members of the Nigerian Legion to partner with it in achieving the Green Money (G-M) initiative. The Commissioner for Information and Orientation, Mr. Asu Okang made the call yesterday during the 2020 Laying of Remembrance Wreath at the Millennium Park (Cenotaph). He said the state government had initiated the programme to boost revenue and improve agricultural production in the state. Okang added that the initiative was for the benefit of indigenes and residents, as the government had instituted Cross River State Agricultural Development Company.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .